  "text": "For the yeast and Escherichia coli strains used in this study, see Table 1 . Yeast was grown on either rich YPD (1% yeast extract, 2% peptone, and 2% d-glucose), YPG (3% glycerol), or synthetic complete (SC) media [Sigma-Aldrich, Helsinki, Finland; or Bio101/QBiogene, Carlsbad, CA, USA (SCD 2% d-glucose, SCG 3% glycerol)] or SC media lacking one or more nutrients. Yeast cells were transformed as described previously [CITATION_1] .",
